cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you cite this specification in academic, regulatory, or industrial work, please use the following metadata."
type: software
title: "Marque — a protocol for human correspondence in the age of AI"
abstract: >
  Marque is a cryptographically signed, federated messaging protocol
  proposed as the successor to SMTP and IMAP. It treats identity as a
  portable cryptographic object, encrypts content end-to-end by default
  with MLS (RFC 9420), produces eIDAS 2.0 QERDS-compliant legal proof as
  a tiered option, and bridges bidirectionally to legacy email throughout
  a ten- to twenty-year transition.
